	<title class="- topic/title " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/REST/rest-cluster-joinnode.dita" xtrc="title:1;5:9">Joining nodes into clusters</title>
	<body class="- topic/body " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/REST/rest-cluster-joinnode.dita" xtrc="body:1;6:8">
		<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/REST/rest-cluster-joinnode.dita" xtrc="p:1;7:6">This is a REST request made to an individual Couchbase node to add that node to a given
			cluster. You cannot merge two clusters together into a single cluster using the REST
			API, however, you can add a single node to an existing cluster. You will need to provide
			several parameters to add a node to a cluster.</p>
		
		<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/REST/rest-cluster-joinnode.dita" xtrc="p:2;12:6">The following arguments are required:</p>
		
